1. Install python from official site
2. Run "pip install requests" and "pip install flask" in powershell
3. Go to Openweather website and create your own api
4. Open weather.pyw file with VS Code
5. Put your API key in line 24, where it is written "YOUR API KEY"
6. Put your city name
7. Save the file
8. Copy weather.pyw file 
9. Go to C:\Users\%USER NAME%\AppData\Roaming\Microsoft\Windows\Start Menu\Programs\Startup
10. Paste the weather.pyw file as shortcut
11. Load taskbar clock customization mod from windhawk
